sentences: Esther Scliar (28 September 1926 – 18 March 1978) was a Brazilian pianist and composer.

Esther spent the first years of her life in Rivera, Uruguay, but her parents separated and Scliar moved with her father to Passo Fundo where she and her sister were raised by their aunt, Jayme Scliar Kruter.
In 1950 she attempted suicide, and later became a militant affiliated with the Communist Youth of the PCB.
In 1952 she studied choral conducting with Nilda Müller in Montevideo and founded and was the first conductor of the Choir of the Musical Youth Association of Porto Alegre.
In 1966 she wrote the music for the movie The Loss of Mario Fiorani and received an award for  "Best Song" at the Brazilian Film Week II.

In 1952 she found she had contracted tuberculosis, and in 1968 she had a stroke and left her position at Villa-Lobos Institute.
